DWF Package API
[DWF Toolkit Components]

Collaboration diagram for DWF Package API:

Detailed Description

The classes and interfaces that make up this module provide the basic I/O functionality for the DWF package file. These fall roughly into three categories:

  • Data Objects that define the transient state to the elements of DWF and provide streaming access to their content.

  • Package Readers that can process compressed DWF package files and streams, and their resources and provide fast, flexible processing of the XML data documents therein. Schema-driven parsers can be used as-is, hooked and filtered or or replaced entirely with custom implementations.

  • Package Writers that produce highly compressed and optimally ordered DWF package files; including optional version extensions for maximum support and compatability.
